5.0     Major Release - Modern Web UI & Security

    BREAKING CHANGES
    * Remove legacy form-urlencoded POST command API
      - External scripts using commands like `command=restart&camid=1` will break
      - Migrate to new JSON REST API endpoints (see API CHANGES below)

    API CHANGES
    * Replace legacy POST commands with JSON REST API endpoints:
      - POST /0/api/config/write (replaces command=config_write)
      - POST /{camId}/api/camera/restart (replaces command=restart)
      - POST /{camId}/api/camera/snapshot (replaces command=snapshot)
      - POST /{camId}/api/camera/pause with {"action":"on|off|schedule"}
      - POST /{camId}/api/camera/stop (replaces command=stop)
      - POST /{camId}/api/camera/event/start (replaces command=eventstart)
      - POST /{camId}/api/camera/event/end (replaces command=eventend)
      - POST /{camId}/api/camera/ptz with {"action":"pan_left|pan_right|..."}
    * All new endpoints require X-CSRF-Token header for CSRF protection
    * All new endpoints return JSON responses: {"status":"ok"} or {"error":"..."}

    PLATFORM REQUIREMENTS
    * Raspberry Pi 4 or newer required (64-bit only)
    * Raspberry Pi 3 and older NOT supported due to:
      - libcamera API changes requiring newer GPU firmware
      - 64-bit OS requirement (armhf/32-bit deprecated)
      - Insufficient RAM for bcrypt + multi-camera workloads
    * Tested platforms: Raspberry Pi 4, Raspberry Pi 5

    AUTHENTICATION & SECURITY
    * Implement bcrypt password hashing with work factor 12 (webu_auth.hpp/cpp)
    * Add CLI setup tool for password configuration (motion-setup binary)
    * Support --reset flag for password recovery
    * Support --config flag for alternate config file paths
    * Add auto-detection of bcrypt vs plaintext passwords (backward compatible)
    * Add auto-hashing for password changes via Settings UI
    * Fix admin username to "admin" to prevent username enumeration attacks
    * Add CSRF protection with per-session tokens
    * Add session-based authentication with 64-char cryptographic tokens
    * Add configurable session timeout (webcontrol_session_timeout parameter)
    * Add sliding window session expiration
    * Log warnings when plaintext passwords detected

    WEB UI (React)
    * Complete React 18 + TypeScript + Vite web interface
    * Implement AuthGate component for protected routes
    * Implement LoginPage with session management
    * Add Settings page with readonly admin username field
    * Implement live camera streaming via MJPEG
    * Add thumbnail display for folder-based media browsing
    * Implement snapshot button for manual image capture
    * Add folder-based media browsing with delete-all functionality

    RASPBERRY PI 5 SUPPORT
    * Raspberry Pi 5 + Camera Module v3 (IMX708) native support
    * Change libcamera StreamRole from Viewfinder to VideoRecording for Pi 5 PiSP
    * Add multi-buffer support for libcamera with configurable buffer count
    * Add camera filtering to exclude USB cameras from CSI camera detection
    * Add model-based camera selection for libcamera devices
    * Add libcam_buffer_count configuration parameter (default: 4)

    CONFIGURATION SYSTEM REFACTOR
    * Major configuration system refactor for improved performance
    * Add O(1) parameter registry with hash map lookup (parm_registry.hpp/cpp)
    * Add scoped parameter structs for reduced memory footprint (parm_structs.hpp)
    * Add O(1) scoped copy operations (copy_app, copy_cam, copy_snd)
    * Separate file I/O from configuration storage (conf_file.hpp/cpp)
    * Replace linear array iteration with registry-based lookups in conf.cpp
    * Integrate O(1) registry lookups into edit_set_active() and parms_copy()
    * Add movie_encoder_preset config parameter for H.264 encoding

    BUILD SYSTEM
    * Add libxcrypt detection in configure.ac for bcrypt support
    * Add motion-setup to bin_PROGRAMS in Makefile.am
    * Add webu_auth.cpp/hpp to motion_SOURCES

    DOCUMENTATION
    * Add authentication setup documentation to README.md
    * Add deployment guide (doc/project/DEPLOYMENT.md)
    * Add architecture documentation (doc/project/ARCHITECTURE.md)
    * Add implementation patterns guide (doc/project/PATTERNS.md)
    

